50|$|GOOS (<b>Global</b> Ocean <b>Observing</b> <b>System)</b> is a <b>global</b> {{system for}} {{sustained}} {{observations of the}} ocean comprising the oceanographic component of the <b>Global</b> Earth <b>Observing</b> <b>System</b> of Systems (GEOSS). GOOS is administrated by the Intergovernmental Oceanographic Commission (IOC), and joins the <b>Global</b> Climate <b>Observing</b> <b>System,</b> GCOS, and <b>Global</b> Terrestrial <b>Observing</b> <b>System,</b> GTOS, as fundamental building blocks of the GEOSS.|$|R
