40|$|In May 2014, the Euro-Argo {{research}} infrastructure became a new European legal entity (Euro-Argo ERIC). The {{objective of the}} Euro-Argo ERIC is to organize a long term European contribution to the international Argo array of profiling floats. Argo is now the most important <b>global</b> in-situ <b>observing</b> <b>system</b> required to <b>observe</b> and understand {{the role of the}} ocean on the earth climate. Euro-Argo is also an essential component of the in-situ infrastructure required for the Copernicus Marine Environmental Monitoring Service (operational oceanography). Euro-Argo will thus develop European contribution to the <b>Global</b> Ocean <b>Observing</b> <b>System</b> (GOOS) and the <b>Global</b> Climate <b>Observing</b> <b>System</b> (GCOS) ...|$|R
